 \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                        \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                                                        \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                        \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                                                        \n            \n    \n    \n        \n                \n                    \n                        \n                                    \u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eAs we get closer to summer, we\u0026#39;re heading into a new season of phone releases, with heavy hitters expected to come from Samsung and Google. In addition, there\u0026#39;s a pretty good chance that we\u0026#39;re going to see some new wearables from both companies as well, with the Samsung Galaxy Watch 8 and Watch 8 Classic being some of the more exciting ones to look out for.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n    \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"019e-4e2b-8277ae0e38b7\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/galaxy-watch-8-classic-360-renders/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-ultra-feature.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-ultra-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-ultra-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-ultra-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-ultra-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-ultra-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-ultra-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-ultra-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-ultra-feature.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                    \u003cimg width=\"4032\" height=\"2268\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Samsung\u0026#39;s Galaxy Watch Ultra, adorning a wrist\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-ultra-feature.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-ultra-feature.jpg\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhile we\u0026#39;d typically be left guessing what to expect, that isn\u0026#39;t the case this year, with the Galaxy Watch 8 Classic making an alleged early appearance thanks to \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/samsung-galaxy-watch-8-classic-ebay-listing-leak/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ean eBay listing for the product\u003c/a\u003e. As you can imagine, this type of leak is pretty shocking, especially considering that most times all we get are \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/galaxy-watch-8-classic-360-renders/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eearly renders of the device ahead of its launch\u003c/a\u003e. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eOf course, while the images of the product are exciting, it\u0026#39;s also important to get the details, since we can learn a lot just from its specifications. One of the more concerning aspects of the Watch 8 Classic was that it was only going to come in one size. Well, it looks like we\u0026#39;re getting some more confirmation on this front from a relatively reliable source, as \u003ca href=\"https://x.com/MysteryLupin/status/1935045267189080535\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eMysteryLupin on X\u003c/a\u003e has shared that the Galaxy Watch 8 Classic will indeed arrive in just one size, coming in at 46mm (via \u003ca href=\"https://9to5google.com/2025/06/17/galaxy-watch-8-classic-size-report/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e9to5Google\u003c/a\u003e). \u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"this-may-be-a-big-deal-for-some\"\u003e\n                        This may be a big deal for some\n               \u003c/h2\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003e With that said, this information isn\u0026#39;t completely new, as we\u0026#39;ve seen reports on the one-size offering before. However, with another source chiming in, this pretty much solidifies that the Galaxy Watch 8 Classic will be offered in just one size, which could be a bummer to some. The previous Galaxy Watch 6 Classic, which was released a couple of years ago, was made available in two sizes, with a 43mm and 47mm variant. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eMoving over to one size could be a change that\u0026#39;s aimed at capturing those looking for a new replacement for their Galaxy Watch Ultra. In addition to the one size for the Galaxy Watch 8 Classic, MysteryLupin also shares that this model will come with Wi-Fi and LTE, and will be available in two colors: black and white. For most people, this is going to be a huge release, with the rotating bezel being seen as the pinnacle of the Galaxy Watch can offer when it comes to design. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eOf course, there are going to be some major differences this year as well, with the \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/samsung-galaxy-watch-8-may-bring-an-ultra-inspired-squircle-design/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003edevice sporting a \u0026#39;squircle\u0026#39; design\u003c/a\u003e. Whether you love it or hate it, it\u0026#39;s pretty much a given that this watch is going to do some major sales numbers, like most of Samsung\u0026#39;s wearables. If the larger size isn\u0026#39;t your thing, at least you\u0026#39;ll have the option of going with the Galaxy Watch 8, which should come in two sizes. The only real question that remains is how much this thing will cost. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                                            \n\n\n\n\n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
